CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1957, pg. 2 reads: "Must Vacate - This three-story, 14-room house at 3404 Ruthvan St., Lawrenceville, has been ordered vacated because of overcrowding. The Allegheny Health Department found two families, totaling 15 members, crowded into two three-room apartments. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, and women, one wearing a light colored dress and sandles, holding newspaper, gathered in front of a three story house at 3404 Ruthvan Street, Lawrenceville
